div.div:
PATCH: Add EAN validation and extraction method to ShopProducts
Implemented a method in the ShopProducts model to validate EAN-13 codes and extract the product ID. This method rejects invalid EANs and removes the check digit from valid ones. Furthermore, in DeviceController, the newly created method is used to provide additional debug information when a product is not found.

PATCH: Add tax and sale methods to ShopProducts model
Added methods to the ShopProducts model for retrieving the tax percentage and sale reduction value for the product. These methods query the appropriate models and return integer values, defaulting to 0 if no tax or sale data exists.

Add EAN-13 barcode generator to ShopProducts model
A method that generates a valid EAN-13 barcode based on the ID of the product has been added to the ShopProducts model. This uses the Luhn algorithm to calculate the checksum digit, ensuring the generated barcode is valid and can be used for inventory management purposes.

PATCH: Add ProductInventory management and fetch API endpoints
This revision introduces a ProductInventory class and corresponding database migration, including addition and deletion methods. In addition, the ShopProducts model is updated with EAN validation, and product fetching, incrementing, and decrementing functions. Finally, two new API routes are added for fetching and incrementing product inventory.

PATCH: Optimize order payments and expense calculations in AccountingMain
The update enhances how OrderPayment and Accounting sums are computed in AccountingMain.php. Specifically, this patch now breaks down sums by transaction status and limits calculations to transactions in the current year and past month, thereby providing a more precise account of unpaid and expense metrics.
